on in modern Mexico. The author examines responses to suicide and death and disproves the long-held belief that Mexicans possess a cavalier attitude toward suffering.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDeathxSocial aspectszMexicoxHistoryy20th century. 0aMurderzMexicoxHistoryy20th century. 0aSuicidezMexicoxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Latin America / Mexico.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066755440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780520964532?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520964532423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520964532/original  a978-3-11-066755-4  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles